       u'Net bilateral aid flows from DAC donors, Total (current US$)',
       u'Number of neonatal deaths',
       u'Refugee population by country or territory of origin',
       u'Domestic credit to private sector by banks (% of GDP)',
       u'Time to import (days)', u'Secondary education, pupils (% female)',
       u'Out-of-pocket health expenditure (% of total expenditure on health)',
       u'External resources for health (% of total expenditure on health)',
       u'Immunization, measles (% of children ages 12-23 months)',
       u'Health expenditure, public (% of total health expenditure)',
       u'Immunization, DPT (% of children ages 12-23 months)',
       u'Primary education, pupils (% female)',
       u'Adjusted savings: education expenditure (current US$)',
       u'Adjusted savings: education expenditure (% of GNI)',
       u'Newborns protected against tetanus (%)',
       u'Improved water source, urban (% of urban population with access)',
       u'Maternal mortality ratio (modeled estimate, per 100,000 live births)',
       u'Tuberculosis case detection rate (%, all forms)',
       u'Principal repayments on external debt, public and publicly guaranteed (PPG) (AMT, current US$)']]
y = data[u'FSI Score']

In [69]:
## Lasso that sets the coefficients of unimportant features to zero
reg = Lasso(alpha=1.0)
reg.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train)
print "co efficients of different features :", reg.coef_
print "R-Squared value of the model=", reg.score(X_test_scaled,y_test)

In [71]:
## Recursive Feature Elimination in combination with Ridge
estimator = Ridge(alpha=1.0)
selector = RFE(estimator, 5, step=1)
selector = selector.fit(X_train_scaled,y_train)
print "Feature rankings:", selector.ranking_
print "R2 squared value: ", selector.score(X_test_scaled,y_test)

Feature rankings: [12  8 15 13  1  1  7  5  2  3 10 16 14  9  1  1  6  1 11  4]
